## sell-items environment variables (example)
##
## Copy to `.env.local` for local development.
## Never commit real secrets.
##

## ----------------------------
## Better Auth (apps/web)
## ----------------------------
## Required in all environments.
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET="PLEASE_SET_A_32+_CHAR_RANDOM_SECRET"

## Base URL of the web app (used for callbacks/redirects).
BETTER_AUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

## Optional: comma-separated trusted origins (overrides internal defaults).
## Examples:
## - Web: http://localhost:3000
## - Expo dev (web preview): http://localhost:8081
## - Expo dev (Android emulator): http://10.0.2.2:3000
## - Expo dev (native devices): http://<YOUR_LAN_IP>:3000 (use your machine’s LAN IP)
## - Expo deep links (dev): exp://**
##
## NOTE: In this repo we treat origins like production software:
## - No hardcoded dev allowlist in code.
## - You must explicitly list any non-`BETTER_AUTH_URL` origins here.
# BETTER_AUTH_TRUSTED_ORIGINS="http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:8081,http://10.0.2.2:3000,http://192.168.1.50:3000,exp://**"

## ----------------------------
## Database (Postgres + Drizzle)
## ----------------------------
DATABASE_URL="postgres://postgres:postgres@localhost:5435/sellitems"

## ----------------------------
## Expo (apps/native)
## ----------------------------
## Used by `apps/native/lib/auth-client.ts` + `apps/native/lib/api.ts` to locate the web backend.
EXPO_PUBLIC_WEB_BASE_URL="http://localhost:3000"
## For devices/emulators, `localhost` is NOT your dev machine. Examples:
## - iOS simulator: http://localhost:3000 (usually ok)
## - Android emulator: http://10.0.2.2:3000
## - Real device (same Wi‑Fi): http://<YOUR_LAN_IP>:3000 (e.g. http://192.168.1.50:3000)

## Your app deep link scheme (must match Expo config).
EXPO_PUBLIC_APP_SCHEME="sellitems"

